{"id": "EUVD-2023-0051", "enisaUuid": "d3619837-4aed-33e6-816b-a8497074b787", "description": "CairoSVG is an SVG converter based on Cairo, a 2D graphics library. Prior to version 2.7.0, Cairo can send requests to external hosts when processing SVG files. A malicious actor could send a specially crafted SVG file that allows them to perform a server-side request forgery or denial of service. Version 2.7.0 disables CairoSVG's ability to access other files online by default.", "datePublished": "2023-03-20T15:23:31", "dateUpdated": "2025-02-25T14:52:14", "baseScore": 9.9, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:C/C:L/I:H/A:L", "references": ["https://github.com/Kozea/CairoSVG/releases/tag/2.7.0", "https://github.com/Kozea/CairoSVG/security/advisories/GHSA-rwmf-w63j-p7gv", "https://github.com/Kozea/CairoSVG/commit/12d31c653c0254fa9d9853f66b04ea46e7397255", "https://github.com/Kozea/CairoSVG/commit/33007d4af9195e2bfb2ff9af064c4c2d8e4b2b53", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-27586", "https://github.com/pypa/advisory-database/tree/main/vulns/cairosvg/PYSEC-2023-9.yaml"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-27586", "GHSA-rwmf-w63j-p7gv", "PYSEC-2023-9"], "assigner": "GitHub_M", "epss": 0.07, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "af0c2363-c3da-30b4-8cb7-8fd8f72579ba", "product": {"name": "CairoSVG"}, "product_version": "< 2.7.0"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "b51ec20f-be1e-3505-9933-3824efaa05e3", "vendor": {"name": "Kozea"}}], "isExploited": false}